  "text": "Found 5 Go source files in grafana/grafana under pkg/components/loki/ that define and configure HTTP and gRPC client timeout and retry logic.\n\nHTTP CLIENT CONFIGURATION (lokihttp):\n\n1. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go - Config struct defines BackoffConfig and Timeout fields:\n   - BackoffConfig: backoff.Config (line 19) - configures retry backoff behavior\n   - Timeout: time.Duration (line 20) - configures HTTP request timeout\n\n2. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go - HTTP client implementation with timeout and retry/backoff:\n   - Client interface (line 117-122) - defines StopNow() method\n   - client struct (line 125-138) - concrete implementation\n   - StopNow() method (line 376-380) - stops the client without waiting for retries\n   - sendBatch() method (line 290-328) - uses backoff.New() and backoff.Ongoing() for retry logic with backoff\n   - send() method (line 330-367) - sets context timeout using context.WithTimeout() with cfg.Timeout\n   - newClient() method (line 148-186) - sets c.client.Timeout = cfg.Timeout at line 175\n\n3. pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go - Fake client implementation:\n   - Fake struct - mock implementation of Client interface\n   - StopNow() method (line 39) - no-op implementation for testing\n\nGRPC CLIENT CONFIGURATION (lokigrpc):\n\n1. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go - Config struct defines Timeout and Retries:\n   - Retries: uint (line 9) - maximum number of retry attempts\n   - Timeout: time.Duration (line 10) - request timeout duration\n\n2. pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go - gRPC client implementation with retry and timeout:\n   - Client struct (line 17-22) - represents the gRPC client\n   - grpcRetryOption() method (line 82-88) - configures retry interceptor using grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries) at line 85\n   - timeoutCtx() method (line 90-96) - creates context with timeout using context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), c.cfg.Timeout) at line 92\n   - init() method (line 57-71) - initializes client with both retry and TLS options via grpc.NewClient()\n\nKey Findings:\n- HTTP client uses backoff.Config from dskit package for retry/backoff logic combined with context timeouts\n- gRPC client uses go-grpc-middleware's grpcretry.WithMax for retry configuration combined with context timeouts\n- Both clients support timeout configuration at the context level\n- StopNow() is an interface method available in HTTP client to stop without waiting for retries"
}

